UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA, SAN DIEGO

CONSENT TO ACT AS A RESEARCH SUBJECT


Craig McKenzie, Ph.D., is conducting a research study to find out more about how people make judgments and decisions. You have been asked to participate because you are taking a psychology course.



If you agree to be in this study, you will be presented with a series of tasks asking you to make judgments about uncertain facts or events or to indicate your preference regarding choice options. The series of tasks will take less than 30 minutes, and you will receive credit for participating. There will be no direct benefit to you from these procedures.



Participation in this study may involve some risks. These include boredom and fatigue. Research records will be kept confidential. Your confidentiality is maintained by identifying your data by number only (your name is not associated with the data).



If you have questions, you may call Dr. McKenzie at (858) 534-3739. Participation in this study is entirely voluntary; you may refuse to participate or withdraw at any time without penalty You may call the Human Research Protection Program at (858) 246-4777 to inquire about your rights as a research subject or report research-related problems.
